# wincher-mcp — core context

**Wincher SEO** MCP server over stdio. User docs: [README.md](../../README.md). Agents: topic rules under `.cursor/rules/`.

## Identity

- Fork of [chris-tutt/wincher-mcp-server](https://github.com/chris-tutt/wincher-mcp-server)
- Repo: https://github.com/vmandic/wincher-mcp
- Single entry: `wincher_mcp_server.py` — MCP name `wincher-mcp`
- Production API: `https://api.wincher.com` (Bearer `WINCHER_API_KEY`)
- Optional staging: MCP arg `--use-staging` + env `WINCHER_STAGING_API_HOST` (host never in repo)
- Nine read-only tools: websites, keywords, rankings, competitors, SERPs, groups, bulk history, annotations

## Commands (repo root)

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt -r requirements-dev.txt
pytest -q && python -m py_compile wincher_mcp_server.py
```

Configure Claude Desktop or Cursor MCP with **absolute paths** to the venv Python and `wincher_mcp_server.py`. See [docs/SETUP.md](../../docs/SETUP.md).

